<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10031a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10031a">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10031a"> 31(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> fatiguing, very fatiguing</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Il devait y avoir dans chacune d&apos;elles <font color="green">[= &eacute;curies]</font> un homme intelligent pour recevoir les d&eacute;p&ecirc;ches apport&eacute;es par un courrier, les remettre &agrave; un autre courrier, prendre soin des hommes et des chevaux qui arrivaient <mark>fatigu&eacute;s</mark>, et subvenir aux frais. <font color="green">[In each stable there had to be a man smart enough to receive the dispatches brought in by courier, to deliver them to another courier; also to take care of the men and horses that arrived fatigued and meet all expenses.]</font> <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) ?25</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c01011h" href="c01all.htm#c01011h">VI.C.01:011(h)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
